---
import ContentPageLayout from '../../layouts/ContentPageLayout.astro';

const lang = 'en';
---

<ContentPageLayout
  title="Careers - eFlury Consulting"
  description="How eFlury Consulting staffs its projects, who we want to meet, and how to send an initiative application. No advertised openings at the moment — stated honestly."
  lang={lang}
  heroTitle="Careers"
  heroSubtitle="We staff projects as we grow — and we read every initiative application"
  lastUpdated="July 10, 2026"
  keywords="careers eFlury Consulting, jobs AI automation, initiative application, Claude MCP engineer, Power BI, Grenchen"
>
  <div class="info-box">
    <p><strong>Current status:</strong> there are <strong>no advertised openings</strong> right now — we say that plainly, because a careers page pretending otherwise would break everything else this site stands for. The page exists because we staff projects with specialists as demand grows, and we would rather meet good people <em>before</em> we need them. Initiative applications are genuinely welcome.</p>
  </div>

  <h2>How we deliver</h2>
  <p>eFlury Consulting builds AI automation for Swiss SMEs — fixed-price projects on Claude, MCP, and Power BI, run along the published <a href="/en/method/">eflury Method™</a>: named deliverables, decision gates, human-in-the-loop, everything documented. Client work is delivered by specialists we bring in as project volume grows. Deliberately small today; staffed to demand tomorrow.</p>

  <h2>Who we want to meet</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>AI &amp; automation engineers</strong> — you build with Claude, MCP connectors, and TypeScript or Python, and you can show it (repos, projects, write-ups).</li>
    <li><strong>BI &amp; data specialists</strong> — Power BI data modeling, reporting pipelines, data quality.</li>
    <li><strong>Finance practitioners</strong> — you know month-end closes, invoicing, or bexio/ABACUS from the inside and want to automate them rather than endure them.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Clients are Swiss SMEs; working languages are German and English.</p>

  <h2>What you can expect</h2>
  <p>The same principles we publish for clients apply inside: decisions in writing, documentation as part of the work (not an afterthought), fixed scopes instead of heroics, and honest no-gos when something does not fit. Read the <a href="/en/method/">method</a> and the <a href="/en/trust/">trust page</a> — that is the working culture, published.</p>

  <h2>Open positions</h2>
  <p>When a concrete role opens, it will be published here first. Until then: the specialist pool is always open.</p>
  <div class="job-cards">
    <a href="/en/careers/spontaneous-application/" class="job-card">
      <span class="jc-badge">Always open</span>
      <span class="jc-title">Spontaneous Application — Specialist Network</span>
      <span class="jc-meta">AI/Automation · BI &amp; Data · Finance — Grenchen SO / Remote (Switzerland) · Workload by agreement</span>
      <span class="jc-cta">View position &amp; application form →</span>
    </a>
  </div>

  <h2>Initiative application</h2>
  <p>Easiest via the <a href="/en/careers/spontaneous-application/">application form</a> — structured, with uploads for CV and certificates. If you prefer writing: one email to <a href="mailto:me@eflury.com?subject=Initiative%20application">me@eflury.com</a> with the subject "Initiative application" works too. No cover-letter theater — include:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>a short CV or your LinkedIn profile,</li>
    <li>three sentences on what you have built (links beat adjectives),</li>
    <li>what you are looking for and when you are available.</li>
  </ul>
  <p>Every application is read and answered personally — by the person who would work with you, not a system.</p>
</ContentPageLayout>

<style>
  .job-cards {
    margin: 1.25rem 0 0.5rem;
  }

  .job-card {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.35rem;
    background: var(--card-bg);
    border: 1px solid var(--border-color);
    border-radius: 14px;
    padding: 1.4rem 1.6rem;
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: all 0.25s ease;
  }

  .job-card:hover {
    transform: translateY(-2px);
    box-shadow: var(--shadow-md);
    border-color: var(--teal-text);
  }

  .jc-badge {
    align-self: flex-start;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.7rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-full);
    background: var(--action-teal);
    color: white;
    font-size: 0.7rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.5px;
    margin-bottom: 0.35rem;
  }

  .jc-title {
    font-size: 1.15rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--text-primary);
  }

  .jc-meta {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    color: var(--text-secondary);
  }

  .jc-cta {
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-size: 0.92rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--teal-text);
  }
</style>
